<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These regulations are duly enacted according to Paragraph 2 of Article 16 of the National Health Insurance Act (hereinafter referred to as the “Act”).
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The National Health Insurance IC card (hereinafter referred to as the “NHI IC Card”) can only be used by the National Health Insurance (hereinafter referred to as the “NHI”) beneficiaries to receive medical treatment from contracted medical care institutions.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[A beneficiary shall apply to the insurer for the production and issuance of the NHI IC Card by himself or herself in person, another person or a group insurance applicant entrusted by him or her, registered post or online from the date when the beneficiary completes the declaration of insurance subscription by meeting the subscription requirements set forth in Article 8 or 9 of the Act for the first time.
Where a beneficiary’s NHI IC Card is damaged, his or her photo changed, lost, his or her identification information changed or any other reason arises, the beneficiary may apply to the insurer for change or replacement of his or her NHI IC Card according to the preceding paragraph. The insurer may entrust the relevant institution (hereinafter referred to as the “Entrusted Institution”) to receive the application on its behalf.
An online application set forth in the preceding two paragraphs shall be made according to the method publicized in the insurer’s global information website, and the application is only applicable to photo-less NHI IC Cards.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[When applying for the production and issuance, change or replacement of the NHI IC Card, the beneficiary shall fill out an application form and comply with the following requirements:
1. Where an application is made by the applicant himself or herself in person, the original identification document shall be presented to the insurer for verification;
2. Where an application is made by another person or a group insurance applicant entrusted by the applicant, the original identification documents of the applicant and the entrusted person shall be presented to the insurer for verification;
3. Where an application is made via post or the Entrusted Institution, the identification document shall be submitted to the insurer for verification.
4. Where an application is made online, the citizen digital certificate and digital certificate of the entity issued by the respective industry competent authorities shall be used to log into the insurer’s global information website to proceed with the application.
The identification document set forth in the preceding paragraph refers to one of the following documents:
1. National identification card: household registration certificate may replace the national identification card in the case of a person under the age of 14 years old;
2. Passport issued by the Republic of China;
3. Driver’s license of automobile (motorcycle); or
4. Alien resident certificate in compliance with Article 8 of the Enforcement Rules of the National Health Insurance Act.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where a beneficiary applies to the insurer for the NHI IC Card, he or she shall pay a fee according to the requirement. Nonetheless, the above fee should be exempted if any of the following circumstances occurs:
1. The beneficiary applies for his or her first NHI IC Card; or
2. The basic information stored in the NHI IC Card cannot be accessed because there is an error in its production by the insurer, the card and the chip are bent, cracked due to scratch or undue pressure or deformed, or detachment, change of color or wear and tear of the chip occurs, which is not caused by human conduct.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Data which may be stored from the NHI IC Card includes the basic information, the NHI data, medical service data and health administration data with the data column of each storage area listed in Table 1.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[A beneficiary may set up a password on his or her NHI IC Card to restrict the access to his or her personal NHI data, data of medical services and data of health administration.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The insurer shall install NHI IC Card readers in all of its regional branch offices, liaison offices and all township (town, city, district) administrations for beneficiaries to inquire and update data as well as settings which are stored in their NHI IC Cards or change their passwords on their NHI IC Cards.
Where a beneficiary forgets his or her own NHI IC Card password, he or she may apply to the insurer for re-setting the password. The beneficiary shall make the application in person by presenting the original identification document, or, alternatively, make the application via post or facsimile by submitting a copy of the identification document. The insurer shall proceed with the application after it verifies the beneficiary’s identity.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 9</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[After the contracted medical care institution provides medical services for a beneficiary or verifies the NHI IC Card of such beneficiary, it shall key in the medical records of the current medical visit in the NHI IC Card of the beneficiary. Notwithstanding, the above may not apply in the case stipulated in Note 3 of Table 1.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 10</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The contract medical care institutions shall upload the medical records to the insurer for future reference through the Virtual Private Network within 24 hours after they key in the medical records in the NHI IC Cards of the beneficiaries. Notwithstanding, the above may not apply in the event of force majeure or special circumstance approved by the insurer.
The medical records in the preceding paragraph which are required to be uploaded to the insurer are set forth in Table 2.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 11</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The contracted medical care institutions shall access the medical records which is already stored in the NHI IC Card or uploaded to the insurer based on the medical needs when they provide medical services for beneficiaries. Notwithstanding, the medical care institutions may not access the aforementioned records if a beneficiary sets up a password to restrict the access to data stored in his or her own NHI IC Card.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 12</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The NHI IC Card shall contain six credits for medical treatments which will expire on the next birthday of a beneficiary.
A beneficiary may update the credits for medical treatments at a NHI IC Card reader which the insurer has installed within one month from his or her birthday every year or, alternatively, the contracted medical care institution takes initiative to update the beneficiary’s NHI IC Card when he or she seeks medical services during that period of time.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 13</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where any of the following circumstances occurs, the NHI IC Card of a beneficiary shall be updated at the NHI IC Card reader installed in the contracted medical care institutions or the insurer:
1. The NHI IC Card expires or has zero credit for medical treatment;
2. The beneficiary acquires or loses the status of a low-income household member, veteran, household representative of survivors of veterans;
3. The proof of major illness and injury of the beneficiary is acquired, revoked or cancelled upon the notice of the insurer;
4. The registration and change of organ donation or hospice palliative care; or
5. Any other medical need which is recorded.
Where the insurer provides medical visit advice to a beneficiary, it may request the beneficiary to update his or her credits for medical treatment at a designated place.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 14</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[After a beneficiary receives the replaced NHI IC Card, his or her original NHI IC Card is automatically revoked and is no longer valid.
Where a beneficiary withdraws from the NHI according to Article 13 of the Act, the NHI IC Card held by the beneficiary should no longer be used. When the cause for the withdrawal from the NHI ceases to exist and the beneficiary is required to re-subscribe to the NHI according to the law, his or her NHI IC Card can be reinstated for use after being updated according to the preceding Article.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 15</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The insurer may only use the data keyed in and uploaded from the contracted medical care institutions for the following purposes:
1. Management and audit of abnormal medical visits of beneficiaries or abnormal diagnosis and treatment behaviors of physicians;
2. Real-time advice for beneficiaries who are high users of medical services;
3. Management of abnormal drug use by beneficiaries; and
4. Coordination with disease prevention and health related policies.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 16</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The insurer shall take the following measures in respect of data which is uploaded by the contracted medical care institutions:
1. Put into place strict information security mechanism and formulate standard operation procedure for the information system which stores and utilizes such data, and carry out the implementation in strict compliance;
2. Construct monitoring and management mechanism which ensures transmission quality, security and efficiency of connections of the Virtual Private Network;  and
3. Install proper mechanism to protect the originally uploaded data and internally processed data from being accessed by unauthorized personnel. A staff should be properly authorized before accessing the data.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 17</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These regulations shall come into force on January 1, 2013.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
